<TITLE> AL leader arrested in Rangpur </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Rangpur, August 6 (bdnews24.com) Rangpur police arrested an Awami League leader Monday noon from Pirganj press club premises during a sit-in strike called demanding the freedom of Sheikh Hasina. Makbul Hossain, Pirganj police chief told bdnews24.com, "Nazimuddin, president of Panchgachhi union committee of the Awami League was arrested on charges of violating the Emergency Powers Rules. Preparations are ongoing for filing a case against him in this connection." Nazimuddin, 57, was arrested at 12 noon from Pirganj press club after he started a sit-in strike at 11 am hoisting a banner sporting "We want Sheikh Hasina's freedom" message on it, Pirganj press club general secretary Sirajul Islam told bdnews24.com. "Nazimuddin, a Liberation War veteran didn't shout any slogan. He just resorted to a peaceful sit-in strike there at the club. The police came and picked him up at 12:05 pm," said Islam. Sirajul Islam added that Nazimuddin had been observing silent protestation by donning black clothes since Hasina's detention in July. Nazimuddin, son of Osman Ghani hails from Paikan village under Panchgachhi union. bdnew
